qas.question: When was a military coup conducted?
When did the mutiny of military factions occur?

answers.text: the head of the armed forces

context: In <a0_0>September 2003<a0_0/>, a military coup was conducted. The military arrested <a1_0>Ialá<a1_0/> on the charge of being "unable to solve the problems". After being delayed several times, legislative elections were held in <a2_0>March 2004<a2_0/>. A mutiny of military factions in <a3_0>October 2004<a3_0/> resulted in the death of <a4_0>the head of the armed forces<a4_0/> and caused widespread unrest.
